			<tr>
				<td width="100%"><a href="viewtopic.php?p=25958&amp;sid=611672fb646392e9f90973967b8806f8#25958"><img src="templates/subSilver/images/icon_minipost.gif" width="12" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" border="0" /></a><span class="postdetails">Posted: Sun Feb 16, 2003 10:01 am<span class="gen">&nbsp;</span>&nbsp; &nbsp;Post subject: Relevant extracts from Healer TL report</span></td>
				<td valign="top" align="right" nowrap="nowrap"><a href="posting.php?mode=quote&amp;p=25958&amp;sid=611672fb646392e9f90973967b8806f8"><img src="templates/subSilver/images/lang_english/icon_quote.gif" alt="Reply with quote" title="Reply with quote" border="0" /></a>   </td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><hr /></td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Some interesting things in Moller's latest Healer TL report:
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Old Issue:</span> Healers (and other classes) are still waiting for the implementation of a system that awards Realm Points for mez, stun, root and debuff spells. 
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Interrupts:</span>
<br />

<br />
Pet level in RvR is being treated as Controller level for purposes of interrupts. A level 20 pet controlled by a level 50 character will interrupt as if the pet were level 50 – 100% interrupt rate. From testing it appears that level 35-36 players will interrupt a level 50 caster 40% of the time. Pets should be treated as the pet level, not controller’s level.
<br />

<br />
Interrupting a player with an amnesia spell is problematic. If the amnesia spell lands, the player’s current spell is interrupted, but they do not receive the interrupt timer (you must wait x seconds before casting again) and can immediately start casting again. HOWEVER if they RESIST the spell, they get the interrupt timer. It is more beneficial for your target to interrupt an amnesia spell (a spell specifically designed to interrupt) than it is for the spell to land. This makes no sense.
<br />

<br />
Crowd Control spells interrupt players. Crowd control spells also interrupt players that are IMMUNE to that type of Crowd Control. If I get mezzed, and I purge, I am now mez immune for 60 seconds. However, if a player is chain casting mez on me, I will be unable to cast because I am interrupted by a spell I am immune to.
<br />

<br />
Interrupts are different in RvR than they are in PvE. Completely different. It is not possible to cast while an equal level player is meleeing you in RvR. Absolutely impossible. However, it is very easy to cast between swings of an equal level mob. It is even possible to cast between swings of a higher level mob. This is easily apparent with Albion Relic Keep guards. They have huge 2h swords that hit hard and swing once every 5 seconds. You can cast between the swings of the sword easily. That is impossible in RvR. Even facing a Troll using a 6.0 speed two-handed axe that has been debuffed with a 40% attack speed debuff so that he is swinging once ever 8 seconds will prevent you from getting a single spell off. This is absurd.
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-style: italic">To summarize what needs to be changed in terms of interrupts:</span>
<br />

<br />
-Pets should be treated as the level of the pet when determining chance to interrupt.
<br />
-Spells that are resisted should not interrupt.
<br />
-You should not be interrupted by a spell that you are immune to.
<br />
-RvR interrupts should function identically to PvE interrupts.
<br />

<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Resists:</span>
<br />

<br />
Resists are out of hand. The ability for groups to routinely have 50% to all magical resists, and for some groups to have 90% to all magical resists for a given encounter is absurd. The diminishing returns resist system proposed by the Magician Team Leads should be implemented as soon as possible. There is a great deal of balancing that cannot be done until resists (and interrupts) are brought down to a reasonable level. Before that is done, the majority of attempts at balancing will be futile.
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Mending</span> 
<br />

<br />
Color code the group (and mini) window so that it is obvious when group members have status ailments that can be cured. The suggestions on the Druid TL report are ideal – Green for Poison, Orange for Disease and Yellow for Mez. 
<br />

<br />
- - - - - - - - -
<br />

<br />
Interestingly the main issues with healers are now pretty close to our main issues! Meaning:
<br />

<br />
- RPs for mez root and debuff
<br />
- Change interrupts (so a caster has some chance of casting whilst being attacked)
<br />
- Lessen resists
<br />

<br />
Any of these improvements would help sorcs a lot as well as healers (except changing pet interrupts to be based on the pet level). So, even though we may be coming to the end of Alb's improvements, if Mythic turns to Midgard next and Healers get this help then we should do very well out of it too.
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
For now it's the bugs are most interesting, as they give us a few ways to cause trouble:
<br />

<br />
- it's worth snagging any pet if you don't have one since it'll be great for interrupting even if it can't do any damage.
<br />

<br />
- AoE mez interrupting even with the timer gone makes the aoe mez (esp with bolt range) a good way of upsetting a mass of casters and healers even if they have already been missed.
<br />

<br />
- AoE amnesia: it makes the lower level spells much better, as, although they have a smaller radius, they have a higher chance of resisting and causing a true interrupt, and use a lot less power. 
<br />

<br />
One thing that's irritating is that the healer attack speed debuff interrupts. Given that this is an insta this gives the healer 3 instas to interrupt with (also mez and stun). Our instas do not interrupt yet the healer's does. Having seen healers discuss this I know plenty of healers use this spell to interrupt casters (clearly lowering a casters attack speed is useless). Considering how quickly Mythic fixed our instas when they interrupted (never made it to a live patch) it's surprising that they left the healer's insta debuff un-fixed.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
